106-114 West 26th Street, south side, west of Sixth Avenue. 1914.

James Suydam.

(1)
Sixth Ave., west side, north from, but not including West 26th Street. In the background, can be seen the 28th Street station of the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line. Note the man with the advertising sign sitting on a barrel. This is not an uncommon sight in this section of the city.

December 24, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
